<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" ><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="3.7.3">Jekyll</generator><link href="http://localhost:4000/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><link href="http://localhost:4000/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><updated>2018-10-19T23:01:05+05:30</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/</id><title type="html">Abhishek Shastri</title><subtitle>I am a web developer and love to build things.</subtitle><entry><title type="html">Welcome to Development of Jekyll</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/blog/Welcome-to-alt-campus" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Welcome to Development of Jekyll" /><published>2018-09-03T12:21:38+05:30</published><updated>2018-09-03T12:21:38+05:30</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/blog/Welcome-to-alt-campus</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/blog/Welcome-to-alt-campus">&lt;p&gt;Start your journey of Web development from scratch using jekyll.&lt;br /&gt;
For this you need to learn few basic things as mentioned below…&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-ruby&quot; data-lang=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;no&quot;&gt;Ruby&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;installed&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;on&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;your&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;computer&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;sudo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;apt&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;get&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;install&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;ruby&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;no&quot;&gt;Install&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;jekyll&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;sudo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;apt&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;get&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;install&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;jekyll&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;no&quot;&gt;Install&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;no&quot;&gt;Bundler&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;sudo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;apt&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;get&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;install&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;bundler&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sometimes we may face difficulties in installing the above things.&lt;br /&gt;
If you face &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nokogiri.org/&quot;&gt;nakogiri&lt;/a&gt; problem then use following command&lt;br /&gt;
      -sudo apt-get install build-essential&lt;br /&gt;
      -sudo apt-get install build-essential patch ruby-dev zlib1g-dev liblzma-dev&lt;br /&gt;
      -sudo gem install nakogiri&lt;br /&gt;
      -bundle install&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html">Start your journey of Web development from scratch using jekyll. For this you need to learn few basic things as mentioned below… 1. Ruby installed on your computer sudo apt-get install ruby 2. Install jekyll sudo apt-get install jekyll 3. Install Bundler sudo apt-get install bundler Sometimes we may face difficulties in installing the above things. If you face nakogiri problem then use following command -sudo apt-get install build-essential -sudo apt-get install build-essential patch ruby-dev zlib1g-dev liblzma-dev -sudo gem install nakogiri -bundle install</summary></entry></feed>